# Pong-RN Game Improvement Plan

Investigation and implementation roadmap. **Priority: HUD board â€” centered horizontally in both orientations.** Landscape court layout stays as-is; scoreboard top-center on court. Portrait gets a dedicated top HUD (score centered in bar) + smaller play board. Free rotation on intro/win screens; **locked during active play**.

### Scoreboard rule (both orientations)

- Score row (`AI | score : score | You`) is **horizontally centered** always
- **Landscape:** scoreboard **top-center** on court (`alignItems: 'center'`, `justifyContent: 'flex-start'`)
- **Portrait:** scoreboard centered within the top HUD bar (not left-aligned)

### Gameplay rule (orientation-specific axes)

| | **Landscape** | **Portrait** |
|---|---------------|--------------|
| AI paddle | Left â€” moves vertically | Top â€” moves horizontally |
| Player paddle | Right â€” drag vertically | Bottom â€” drag horizontally |
| Ball | Moves horizontally; bounces top/bottom walls | Moves vertically; bounces left/right walls |
| Scoring | Ball exits left (you score) / right (AI scores) | Ball exits top (you score) / bottom (AI scores) |
| Court aspect | Full flex court, 5% side margins | Fixed 9:16 tall court below HUD (`COURT_ASPECT_RATIO_PORTRAIT`) |

### Orientation rule

| Screen state | Rotation |
|--------------|----------|
| Intro (`StartOverlay`) | Free â€” portrait â†” landscape |
| Win (`WinOverlay`) | Free |
| Active play (`gameStarted && !winner`) | **Locked** to orientation at game start |
| Pause overlay | Locked (still in active match) |

Mid-game live relayout was removed after device QA showed broken paddle positions and missing balls. `expo-screen-orientation` locks the device during play; a `RotationLockedBanner` appears (with brief auto-pause) if the player physically rotates the device.

