## Phase5 â€” Flexible Orientation Transitions âś…

**Goal:** Correct behavior when user rotates between screens; stable gameplay during a match.

### Decision (revised)

Initial approach: debounced mid-game restart (`resetActiveGame`) on orientation change. **Device QA failed** â€” paddles kept portrait Y positions in landscape, ball could disappear, layout loops caused "Maximum update depth exceeded".

**Current approach:** Lock orientation for the duration of an active match. Free rotation on intro and win screens only.

### Intro / win rotation flow

```
orientation change (!gameStarted || winner !== null)
  â†’ useLayoutEffect:
      isPortraitSV updated
      setCourtBounds(null)   // avoid stale overlay frame
  â†’ court onLayout:
      updateCourtBounds (guarded)
      syncCourtMetrics + positionPaddles
  â†’ portrait: overlay reframes via CourtOverlayFrame + courtBounds
  â†’ landscape: fullScreenOverlay on playArea (centered Start/Win/Pause; compact layout)
  â†’ court key={portrait|landscape} forces remeasure on orientation flip
```

### Active play flow

```
gameStarted && !winner
  â†’ lockedGameplayPortrait set in startGame / playAgain
  â†’ useGameplayOrientationLock(lockedPortrait):
      lockAsync(PORTRAIT_UP | LANDSCAPE)
      accelerometer baseline tilt (normalized gravity angle via expo-sensors)
      + Dimensions / ScreenOrientation listeners as fallback
  â†’ on physical rotate (~32Â° from baseline) or UI dimension mismatch:
      RotationLockedBanner (4s, safe-area bottom padding)
      isPaused = true (auto-resume when banner dismisses)
      haptic warning; re-lock orientation
  â†’ on unlock: intro screen or win overlay
```

